org.jscsi.target.scsi.inquiry
Enum ProtocolIdentifier

      org.jscsi.target.scsi.inquiry.ProtocolIdentifier
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<ProtocolIdentifier>
public enum ProtocolIdentifier
extends Enum<ProtocolIdentifier>

The PROTOCOL IDENTIFIER field is part of IDENTIFICATION DESCRIPTORS and may indicate the SCSI transport protocol to which the identification descriptor applies. If the ASSOCIATION field contains a value other than 01b (i.e., target port) or 10b (i.e., SCSI target device) or the PIV bit is set to zero, then the PROTOCOL IDENTIFIER field contents are reserved. If the ASSOCIATION field contains a value of 01b or 10b and the PIV bit is set to one, then the PROTOCOL IDENTIFIER field shall contain one of the values defined in the following table to indicate the SCSI transport protocol to which the identification descriptor applies.

Protocol
Identifier		 Description Protocol
Standard
0x0 Fibre Channel FCP-2
0x1 Parallel SCSI SPI-5
0x2 SSA SSA-S3P
0x3 IEEE 1394 SBP-3
0x4 SCSI Remote Direct Memory Access Protocol SRP
0x5 Internet SCSI (iSCSI) iSCSI
0x6 SAS Serial SCSI Protocol SAS
0x7 Automation/Drive Interface Transport Protocol ADT
0x8 AT Attachment Interface (ATA/ATAPI) ATA/ATAPI-7
0x9-0xe RESERVED
0xf No speficif protocol
The PROTOCOL IDENTIFIER field has a length of four bits.

Andreas Ergenzinger
